Day 7 - Deployed a virtual cisco lab and deploying a multilayer switch then connecting it with 2 different laptops using ethernet cables (virtual) with a copper straight through cable, then configured the ipv4 
to 192.168.1.1 (Laptop 1) then automatically set subnet mask to 255.255.255.0. Also changed the Mac address of the Laptops wish 0001.1111.1111. For Laptop 2 I changed the ipv4 to 192.168.1.2 then the subnet mast is the same.
For both Laptops, I changed the default gateway to 192.168.1.254 then changed the DNS Server to 8.8.8.8 (google's dns). For the switch, I inserted a AC-POWER-SUPPLY at the back for it to turn on. I executed
a few commands like pinging each laptop with it's IP the command ping (ip) then it should send a feedback. Also some few commands like ipconfig, ipconfig /all to see the mac address of the device. 
